fn.p: Different Essential Oil samples were identified progressively using letters from P–Z and AA–AF. (l) leaves, (be) berries, (br) branches, (f) flowers, (r) resin, (g) galls. RT: retention time. Values are percent of the total oil composition. 1 4-chloro-2-phenylaniline. 2 Benzene-methoxy-trimethyl-tetrahydro-halenedica-urs-12-en-28-al; 3 4,12-bis(hydroxymethyl)-2,2-metac-4,14-bis(hydroxymethyl)-2,2-metac-1-oxo-2,3,5,6,7,8-hexahydrothienol.
